## Module 4: Stashing
- **Scenario:** Used when you need to switch branches to fix a hotfix without committing incomplete "work-in-progress" code.
- **Commands:**
  - `git stash`: Saves changes to a temporary area and clears the working directory.
  - `git stash list`: Shows your saved stashes.
  - `git stash pop`: Restores changes and removes them from the stash list.
  - `git stash apply`: Restores changes but keeps them in the list.

  Command|History Impact|Use Case
git revert|"Adds a new ""undo"" commit."|Public/Shared branches (avoids breaking teammates' repos).
git reset|Physically deletes commits.|Private/Local branches (cleaning up your own mess).